Package io.neba.api.annotations

  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    Children
    Provides a Collection, List or Set of children of the resource.
    Path
    Defines the relative or absolute path of a property or resource mapped to a field.
    PostMapping
    Methods of a ResourceModel with this annotation are invoked after all properties have been mapped from the model's resource.
    PreMapping
    Methods of a ResourceModel with this annotation are invoked before any properties have been mapped from the model's resource.
    Reference
    Marks a field as containing a reference, i.e.
    ResourceModel
    A resource model is a Component representing sling resources with specific sling resource types, JCR primary node types or mixin types.
    ResourceParam
    Marks a parameter of a Spring @RequestMapping method as containing a resource path.
    SelfTest
    Methods annotated with SelfTest are considered selftests of a service component and are automatically detected.
    Selftest methods must adhere to the following conventions:
    They must be applied to a public void method without arguments The annotated bean must have application scope (i.e.
    This
    Marks a field as representing the resource represented by the current ResourceModel.
    Unmapped
    Excludes a field from the resource-to-model mapping.
